The Eko Electricity Distribution Company yesterday announced four hours daily power interruption in Ikoyi and other adjoining areas in Lagos Island for the next one week. Mr. Godwin Idemudia, the General Manager, Corporate Communications of the company, who disclosed this in a statement said the week-long power interruption was for the purpose of carrying out service improvement rehabilitation work on Shaw road 11kv feeder covering Ikoyi and environs. He said that the proposed rehabilitation work would enhance better service delivery to the company’s customers in the area. The EKEDC spokesman appeal to all residents of the affected area to please bear with the situation, while customers of the company’s strive to make the satisfaction of its customers its utmost priority. comments Do you get a good or bad response from your wife after making love? Discover a great natural solution that changed my story and put an end to weak/premature ejaculation, CLICK HERE. 